 First a survey is given about current research regarding psychosocial factors in infertility. The need for psychological counselling for infertile couples will be discussed as well as the available concepts of psychological counselling. The two-step counselling concept of the "Heidelberg Fertility Consultation Service" is presented. The main results of the counselling study are reported as well as the effects of infertility counselling from the patient's point of view. Psychological counselling in infertile couples should help the couple to cope with this critical life event and with the medical treatment.  
